{"id":1192142439,"question_id":3347,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"3 months, 1 week","timestamp":1709433462,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1192142439/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Distribute Elements Into Two Arrays I","memory":"44.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int[] resultArray(int[] nums) {\n        \n        int len = nums.length;\n        \n        List<Integer> arr1= new ArrayList<>();\n        List<Integer> arr2= new ArrayList<>();\n        \n        arr1.add(nums[0]);\n        arr2.add(nums[1]);\n        \n        for(int i=2; i<len; i++){\n            \n              if(arr1.get(arr1.size()-1)>arr2.get(arr2.size()-1)){\n                  arr1.add(nums[i]);\n              } else\n                  arr2.add(nums[i]);\n        }\n        \n        int idx=0, i1=0, i2=0;\n        \n        while(i1<arr1.size()){\n            nums[idx++] = arr1.get(i1++);\n        }\n        \n        while(i2<arr2.size()){\n            nums[idx++] = arr2.get(i2++);\n        }\n        \n        \n        return nums;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"distribute-elements-into-two-arrays-i","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
